  "text": "Linkage strength between educational outcomes and occupational positions should also affect the risk of unemployment. Sociologists who study comparative educational systems have argued that workers in countries with strong vocational systems have reduced unemployment risk early in their careers [CITATION_1] . We expect this to hold even more strongly when considering the context of specific pathways, rather than the country as a whole, as the contextual unit of analysis.",
